main event: A brightly colored, blue-white object was observed traveling quickly across the sky in Middletown, Kentucky on January 19, 1967.
interesting points: The object seemed to burn out and had a blue tail.
The object moved behind and in front of clouds during the sighting.
The object was reported to be silent, with no sound.
The witness estimated the object to be about half the size of a match stick held at arm's length.
The witness described the object as a round white object with some blue in it.
photographs: No photographs included in the report
